document_data.History:
The spell was already known by the time of [[Netheril]], its invention not attributed to any of its arcanists. It was part of all three known schools then. [[Wu jen]] employed the spell as well.

The spell was known to be listed in ''[[the Scalamagdrion]]''{{cite book/Pages from the Mages|92}}{{cite book/Forgotten Realms Campaign Set/DM's Sourcebook of the Realms|190-191}} and the ''[[Tome of Shaping Secrets]]''.{{cite book/The Shattered Statue|14}} ''[[The Scrolls of Ha Rahni]]'', written by a wu jen from [[Kara-Tur]], bore the spell as well.{{cite book/Kara-Tur: The Eastern Realms/Volume I|63}} The insane lichnee [[Druth Daern]] of [[Myth Drannor]] also had this spell in his working spellbook.

By {{yearlink|1358}} it had grown rare;{{cite book/Forgotten Realms Adventures|153}} it was all but forgotten by the {{yearlinkName|1372}}, having been replaced by other, universally more accessible and far more reliable techniques.{{cite book/Player's Handbook v.3.5|92-93}}

document_data.Trivia:
The spell was needed for the focus of the versions of ''[[trap the soul]]'' available by {{yearlink|1357}}.{{cite book/Players Handbook 1st edition|92}} The ''[[demiplane seed]]'' spell best known before {{yearlink|1372}} required a focus prepared using ''enchant an item'', ''[[rope trick]]'', and ''[[distance distortion]]''.{{cite book/A Guide to the Ethereal Plane|39}} The spell was also required to prepare the material component of the ''[[triad gem]]'' spell.{{cite book/Cult of the Dragon|80}}

[[Lightning golem]]s were made using this spell; the hearts of [[stone guardian]]s were also similarly made. The phylacteries of [[dracolich]]es{{cite book/Cult of the Dragon|103}} and of regular [[lich]]es called for ''enchant an item'' in their construction too.{{cite book/Wizard's Spell Compendium Volume Four|1087-1088}}{{cite book/Lords of Darkness|73-74}} Though [[doom guard]]s were not made with this spell, the ''[[anvil of darkness]]'' used to create them was.

[[gray slaad|Grey]] and [[death slaad]]i were known to possess this spell;{{cite book/Monstrous Compendium Planescape Appendix|90-91}} [[red slaad]]i could be enslaved for up to six tasks with a charm made of a pellet removed by ''[[wish]]'', ''[[spiritwrack]]'', and ''[[limited wish]]'', using ''enchant an item''.{{cite book/Fiend Folio 1st edition|81-82}}

Albeit the spell could not ordinarily be cast out of a magical item,{{cite book/The Magister|36}}

The spell took ten times as long in the [[Ethereal plane]],{{cite book/Manual of the Planes 1st edition|18}} and half as long in the [[Inner Planes]].{{cite book/Manual of the Planes 1st edition|28}} It did not work at all in the [[Astral plane]].{{cite dragon/67/The Astral Plane|35}}
